HEADWORD: Penny-a-liner
<hw>Pen"ny-a-lin"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who
furnishes matter to public journals at so much a line; a poor writer for
hire; a hack writer.</def> <rj><au>Thackeray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

